Write-Host 'During application build process, SHA256 hashes are created for each script inside scripts/ folder. This script hash is checked against current hash generated right before execution to make sure that the script file was not altered by someone.<br><br>Build the application and then change the script(scriptAlteration.ps1) inside the resources folder to see the error message.<br><pre>npm run hash<br>npm run build</pre><br>To save you the trouble, it looks like this:<br><span class="error-output">Execution stopped - script file XY has been altered. You little digital rascal!</span>'